09/21/82  read_mail request:  first, f

Syntax:  f {-control_arg}


Syntax as an active request:  [f {-control_arg}]


Function:  prints the message number of the first message of the
specified type; as an active request, returns the message number.


Control arguments:
-include_deleted, -idl
   prints or returns one.  (Ie: the number of the first message in the
   mailbox whether or not it has been deleted.)
-only_deleted, -odl
   prints or returns the message number of the first deleted message.
-only_non_deleted, -ondl
   prints or returns the message number of the first non-deleted
   message in the mailbox.  (Default)


Notes:
If there are no messages of the specified type, the active request will
return the value zero.
